    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Visual works, often windows, or components of visual works or architecture, made of bits or pieces of glass, often chipped along the edges to resemble faceting, set in a matrix of concrete or epoxy resin. The first glass in concrete windows appeared ca. 1929 in Europe; the technique is now used to create other objects as well. For cement reinforced with glass fibers, use "glass reinforced cement."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
